oc:kn_244b4e48 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When designing the dunning communication strategy" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never rely on email alone for dunning notifications. In-app banners and modals are critical — show payment failures on every page load with direct update links." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Email open rates are never 100%; in-app notifications ensure the customer sees the issue during normal product usage" .

oc:kn_395e6071 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PerformanceProfile ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When choosing between smart and manual retry schedules" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Stripe Smart Retries (ML-based) recovers ~15% more than fixed-schedule retries by picking optimal timing from billions of transactions. Prefer provider smart retries over manual schedules when available." ;
    oc:hasRationale "ML-optimized timing accounts for patterns humans can't predict, improving recovery without additional effort" .

oc:kn_4ca1f93b a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:SuccessIndicator ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When evaluating whether the dunning system is working correctly" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Dunning email open rate should be 60%+ and click rate 30%+. Involuntary churn should target 1-2% of MRR/month for early-stage, 0.5-1.5% for growth-stage, and 0.3-0.8% for scale-stage companies." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Low email engagement or high involuntary churn indicates broken dunning flows or poor messaging" .

oc:kn_566d8a0f a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When measuring and benchmarking dunning performance" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Target 50-60% recovery rate for failed payments. Soft decline recovery should be 70%+, hard decline 40%+. Time to recovery should be under 5 days." ;
    oc:hasRationale "These benchmarks distinguish effective dunning from ineffective; below 50% suggests broken retry or communication flows" .

oc:kn_699e2468 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When determining retry strategy for a failed payment" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Classify decline codes as soft (retry: insufficient_funds, generic card_declined, processing_error), hard (don't retry: expired_card, stolen_card), or auth-required. Only retry soft declines 3-5 times over 10-14 days." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Retrying hard declines wastes attempts and can trigger fraud flags; soft declines are temporarily recoverable" ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_801dc8b6 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When configuring post-failure grace period access policies" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Grace period should be 7-14 days after final retry attempt. Full access during grace is recommended for B2B; read-only access for B2C. Immediate lockout is not recommended." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Too short a grace period loses recoverable customers; too long invites exploitation" ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_b8bf6798 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:SideEffect ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When configuring payment gateway — always enable card updater services" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Card updater services (Visa VAU, Mastercard ABU, Amex Cardrefresher) automatically update stored card numbers and expiry dates, reducing hard declines from expired/replaced cards by 30-50%." ;
    oc:hasRationale "This is a zero-effort recovery mechanism that silently prevents a large portion of failures" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_c81ee72a a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Always — start with prevention before building recovery flows" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Pre-dunning (preventing failures before they happen via card updater services, expiry reminders, and backup payment methods) is more effective than recovering failed payments after the fact." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Preventing a failure costs less effort and preserves customer trust better than recovering from one" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

